{{zh-forms|alt=曺,㯥,𣍘}}

===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}

Originally {{zh-l|㯥}}, an {{liushu|ic|nocap=yes}}: two bundles {{zh-l|*東}}. The original meaning is "pair; peer, same kind". Later, {{zh-l|*囗}} was added as a distinguishing mark, which corrupted into {{zh-l|*甘}} in bronze inscriptions and {{zh-l|*曰}} in Seal Script, thus arriving at the intermediate character form {{zh-l|𣍘}}. The top two {{lang|zh|東}} have merged and now resemble {{m|zh|曲}} with an extra stroke.

Unrelated to {{lang|zh|曲}} and {{zh-l|*典}}.

